Presentation 定理二号, Krull PIT 是维数理论中十分重要的一个定理. 用它可以刻画出Noetherian scheme 上的tangent space 的维数大于等于局部维数的性质, 从而定义那些nonsingular 的点. Hartshorne 第一章就有这个定理, 关于tangent space的讨论则被藏在了习题5.10 里面. 值得注意的是Hartshorne 定理1.8A是一个非常不平凡的结果, 这个定理对于finitely generated kkk algebra成立, 然而对于一般的catenary ring, 即任何prime ideal chain 长度相等的ring 却不一定成立, 也挺有意思的. Krull Principal Ideal Theorem In general idea of Zariski tangent space, we have dim⁡Tp,X≥dim⁡Rp\dim \mathbb{T}_{\mathfrak{p},X}\geq \dim R_{\mathfrak{p}}dimTp,X​≥dimRp​, where X=Spec(R)X=\mathrm{Spec}(R)X=Spec(R) and RRR Noetherian. We will prove this in algebraic sense by the Krull’s principal ideal theorem. Recall the Nakayama lemma first: Lemma 1 (Nakayama). For RRR be a ring and R\mathfrak{R}R be its Jacobson radical, a\mathfrak{a}a is an ideal contained in R\mathfrak{R}R. Then For MMM be a finite generated RRR-module, M/aM=0M /\mathfrak{a}M=0M/aM=0 implies M=0M=0M=0. For MMM be a RRR-module, N′N&#x27;N′ is a finite generated submodule of MMM and M=aN′+NM=\mathfrak{a}N&#x27;+NM=aN′+N. Then M=NM=NM=N. For {x1,…,xn}⊂M\{x_{1},\dots,x_{n}\}\subset M{x1​,…,xn​}⊂M satisfies {x1ˉ,…,xnˉ}\{ ar{x_{1}},\dots, ar{x_{n}}\}{x1​ˉ​,…,xn​ˉ​} generates M/aMM /\mathfrak{a}MM/aM, then {x1,…,xn}\{x_{1},\dots,x_{n}\}{x1​,…,xn​} generates MMM. Proof Proof.Omitted. See the textbook.M=aN′+NM=\mathfrak{a}N&#x27;+NM=aN′+N implies M/N=a(N′/N)M /N=\mathfrak{a}(N&#x27; /N)M/N=a(N′/N), so M/NM /NM/N is finitely generated. Then M/N=a(N′/N)⊂a(M/N)⊂M/NM /N=\mathfrak{a}(N&#x27; /N)\subset \mathfrak{a}(M /N)\subset M /NM/N=a(N′/N)⊂a(M/N)⊂M/N, M/N=a(M/N)M /N=\mathfrak{a}(M /N)M/N=a(M/N). By (1), M/N=0M /N=0M/N=0, i.e. M=NM=NM=N.Consider a map f:Rn→Mf:R^{n}	o Mf:Rn→M with f:(r1,…,rn)↦r1x1+⋯+rnxnf:(r_{1},\dots,r_{n})\mapsto r_{1}x_{1}+\cdots+r_{n}x_{n}f:(r1​,…,rn​)↦r1​x1​+⋯+rn​xn​, we want to show fff is surjective, i.e. M/imf=0M /\mathrm{im}f=0M/imf=0. Let π:M→M/aM\pi:M	o M /\mathfrak{a}Mπ:M→M/aM, then aRn⊂ker(π∘f)\mathfrak{a}R^{n}\subset \mathrm{ker}(\pi\circ f)aRn⊂ker(π∘f) so π